# MCP Trust Checker · https://mcptrustchecker.com · support@mcptrustchecker.com · © 2026 Illia Haidar · MIT
cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use MCP Trust Checker or the Capability-Flow Trust Model, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "MCP Trust Checker"
abstract: >-
  Local-first, deterministic security scanner for Model Context Protocol (MCP)
  servers, built on the Capability-Flow Trust Model — an original methodology
  by Illia Haidar that reduces every tool to behavioral roles (untrusted-input,
  sensitive-source, external-sink, code-exec, file-write), wires them into a
  cross-tool toxic-flow graph to statically prove data-exfiltration primitives
  (the lethal trifecta), and produces an auditable, reproducible 0-100 Trust
  Score with a fully itemized penalty vector. No LLM, no account, fully offline.
